irstChangedLine\": 81}, \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777590220756}}\n689:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_pKeZA7QMvmEueEKuSudFCgMR|fc_0f185721c1b445330169f3dfc909788193bf067d68dbfb3ba7\", \"toolName\": \"edit\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.test/arquillian-test-api/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_test/arquillian_test_api/Arquillian_test_apiTest.java.\"}], \"details\": {\"diff\": \"     ...\\n  77         assertThat(urlResource.value()).isEqualTo(URL.class);\\n  78     }\\n  79 \\n  80     @Test\\n+ 81     void lambdaCallbackParametersCanDeclareArquillianResources() throws Exception {\\n+ 82         ResourceUrlFormatter formatter = (@ArquillianResource(URL.class) URL resourceUrl) -> resourceUrl.toExternalForm();\\n+ 83         URL resourceUrl = URI.create(\\\"https://arquillian.example/deployments/app\\\").toURL();\\n+ 84 \\n+ 85         assertThat(formatter.format(resourceUrl)).isEqualTo(\\\"https://arquillian.example/deployments/app\\\");\\n+ 86     }\\n+ 87 \\n+ 88     @Test\\n  81     void annotationContractAllowsRuntimeLookupOnFieldsAndParametersOnly() {\\n  82         Retention retention = ArquillianResource.class.getAnnotation(Retention.class);\\n  83         Target target = ArquillianResource.class.getAnnotation(Target.class);\\n  84 \\n     ...\\n 130         Field field = ResourceConsumer.class.getDeclaredField(fieldName);\\n 131         return field.getAnnotation(ArquillianResource.class);\\n 132     }\\n 133 \\n+142     @FunctionalInterface\\n+143     private interface ResourceUrlFormatter {\\n+144         String format(URL resourceUrl);\\n+145     }\\n+146 \\n 134     private static final class ResourceConsumer {\\n 135         @ArquillianResource\\n 136         private String defaultResource;\\n 137 \\n     ...\", \"firstChangedLine\": 81}, \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777590220756}}\n690:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating enum usage**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether enum constants are functional features. They serve as fields and can represent a fixed Arquillian resource, but ArquillianResource seems designed for injection fields rather than enum constants. That makes me wonder if using enum constants for this purpose is a bit unnatural. I should probably consider how this aligns or diverges from the intended use of ArquillianResource. It's intriguing to ponder the implications involved!\\n\\n**Considering annotation implementation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether a class can implement an annotation interface, and it seems allowed. However, implementing it manually requires the equals/hashCode methods, which leads me to consider how it tests the interface contract and the existing equality standards for annotations. I should explore the issue patterns since the goal is to enhance tests for metadata coverage. Existing tests rely on reflection, but I want to add functional usage to trigger native code. I'll compile carefully, considering new features like `@ArquillianResource` for lambda parameter annotations. This is functional and not already covered by reflection, which is great!\\n\\n**Exploring lambda annotations**\\n\\nI’m looking at a syntax example where I'm using an annotation on a lambda parameter, specifically with the target set to PARAMETER. Yes, I can do this if I'm using explicit types or var. Invoking the callback reads well since it utilizes the annotation public API without relying on reflection. That's a great feature! I wonder if this aligns with Arquillian's intentions from 2015 and whether a formal parameter includes lambda in its considerations. It feels like a different logic flow, which is interesting!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0f185721c1b445330169f3dfab99ac81938d7b675bda217fd9\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp89_JTRvRlTBd5RUPQAP-FmM3Ewxow5Sn9PH84f5E7xAPNdv_m1JY4gn46qpGrTR8fvDzura_uboGqkDYFDAJq7eM8u9T_7R8NneT9JTn0zkBjRZtLFKBAAC7Mjgfzd9NFiVOzRY6pN-QsLbxY7a5zl9HTrzNRaImCzVHMpS5ofoLG4O1tKB3aCpb7k3NA6P_A7ZnTojzH71rAGNHCUfSEgv2synkBTMXVgaxlzITiGsktZt0Z8uwnb9Z21Y05m1KN6hK_LzeUDfW8DidU5JwOeKOm37OUH0W6wm8g0xYxgzlBtvkkCYo7aONPrQWF1qDWQS2trfAyjQi3o1yXKfIiItp7IoZ8T2vwa1WXF9n3B2fVu2xdcokeEWjvJx0k5fRMyNGk1SaFE_C69WwcQfkdKLoWPrUP6pJlEaY1D9RpTzl00ZBENa-pg7ZNVmKSbzpX2_YseUpDer5V5h-UltQrkee1r4iazl_c0UFAPI8pftPqhaTIPHdpPX3WCudXm7draeJrbzLPdcj7zvgRbgDw_SSEAJUxdRHCiAS6Be8mSN3byvBT_qPG1MV92e3bBzV02R3IsSpN6SylT6Bnk3eOfyCkOcVrbPBgTK-dhEUZsiowcjEyViUyloEwbMzB7WnQI3mnltGbqXAS4bl-ouJ1Rs3JCngz6wGaNAzDtLuJXH5YYAwIu7n2MCdGjM2nVixdsUqT-oxzMF9EWk8NyXRvKE_HFtsjiiUPeV2cz42OOY3o0ALSbgmMlmU6kwxZddTJoYRCS7WIq_ZGqOLLc5SMfSgprMu_cKNCks_gHYcEH9PlZlW0YjpoPCXT8xV_nn8ORrEtZkViux_Rh2251d6Yn2LH1Qur3Sat1m3InO6Ln-AUCB2cdgB73hlNx8o9-QVaER7wGWaUXtJay75to91VeRPWTj_CFlHP0fe0Jl2_2IAZxL4kvrgY1i2Ldv6o3R0vT6tWEKf93DW9_MxhpGZjvQIXZJkSU5oXRFSuxzf2ugpL8V8iZD3wkqoIYIeirYVLBWU3u__jGjvFa2lfw5nKr0Su0YQEjZg3AFlYy9fEr_7aCEzXgHVmKurVPHwlSzRYPYDrVCxRn-omnDHVvadoeXAStxiMU8LkCf0W_Z3VZGfFfjvmqnaCnzgq3qvgRzZ2x3upIQCYjcqzFAczlOHyit-h4VGTVX9YGn8tvoVaj62GWP1sAMuFQJ0jtdN8WcY0KXtadGEai1Lsz4fcpVwgN3sq_n2DbXbOyFDUAzZ-eBfnDlyx96i8sSU83qxgqO4iXoyyz33hQzWfRRl_sfmdfj80OEgdH5Ep7zk_ng8yLF7tguk4EpdPz35R9C9qpOsDlTgW3OtfqBiRiwXfabNk3-TI1qnkYv1HbvAV9HmIRLanSBDgz4WtMEA3KcRsQyXcQlutdMjoglNtfeZv1fvNZKnfaLYJ1Eu_228Xok_kmXRGsULh2MMo-X7oRMoI--I-TFL1ynV8ie_GGwE3GC7stFz6maY-Ta3op56DzNzgbjAcSwoz8cKnojaBr49vQ9ZCAVFFwWaKul7pMeBq4E8lFTbx2GNhhu-S9J4IHaTxkr8dL3SaN2vZrNZN80uXVqv7oxXr_FYziEghzAeHqlyTajm_oZ9RxKkDoF3yzcKE-wX7SZLOyQPG-8_14Fhm_Amke1XKpKjW97DYEl6BTiO9edvfUps0aBGO3tVYMffQCxLAhHyqKCOfcrgChki6i5h2D0vNnNg9lG1XmyVwc_rCf3Kmmy0ZuJG9UQXFY66Fpww9eqrBt6rR9BApJ8yqZC3CrvDrzSCLJP5S1ix--0ZckHHW655xRPFQgAddZJ9kMpmmUcvxyd3itHj8orH1YY7pPBrQaQ8-C8p_GbYi1WF_4ZHG13-5_9oYo4Ha1EqPwqKmPiuVqbTYjh4iMY2FzRlD8s97DHHnxWo11nEBUG