{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed to complete this library automatically. Preserved work is available on the branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3763-library-new-request-org.jboss.arquillian.test-arquillian-test-api-1.1.10.Final-a70e7aff\n\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation quality rather than Gradle or metadata plumbing. Artifact discovery, URL population, and checkstyle all succeeded (`human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.arquillian.test:arquillian-test-api:1.1.10.Final/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.arquillian.test:arquillian-test-api:1.1.10.Final/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.arquillian.test:arquillian-test-api:1.1.10.Final/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-30T23-06-25-526882Z.log`). The preserved metrics show 3 iterations, 139 generated LOC, but `tested_library_loc: 0` and `metadata_entries: 0` (`stats/org.jboss.arquillian.test/arquillian-test-api/1.1.10.Final/execution-metrics.json`).\n\nThe generation logs show the run started from a placeholder scaffold and never converged on a strong library-specific test. The first attempt still contained `System.out.println(\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\")` (`human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.arquillian.test:arquillian-test-api:1.1.10.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T23-00-43-355820Z.log`), and the final attempt claims it added a non-reflective public-API test, but the preserved test is still mostly reflection-based and the only new non-reflective method (`lambdaCallbackParametersCanDeclareArquillianResources`) just formats a `URI` string without asserting any `@ArquillianResource` behavior (`human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.arquillian.test:arquillian-test-api:1.1.10.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T23-05-01-338817Z.log`, `tests/src/org.jboss.arquillian.test/arquillian-test-api/1.1.10.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_arquillian_test/arquillian_test_api/Arquillian_test_apiTest.java`). The generated metadata is also empty (`metadata/org.jboss.arquillian.test/arquillian-test-api/1.1.10.Final/reachability-metadata.json` is `{}`) and the dynamic-access stats are 0/0 (`stats/org.jboss.arquillian.test/arquillian-test-api/1.1.10.Final/stats.json`), so there is no useful coverage signal supporting a new metadata entry.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Decide whether `org.jboss.arquillian.test:arquillian-test-api:1.1.10.Final` should be supported at all, given that it appears to be a small annotation-only API and the generated metadata is empty.\n2. If support is still desired, replace the preserved test with a genuinely library-specific public-API test that demonstrates meaningful Arquillian behavior instead of reflection or plain `URI` formatting.\n3. Re-run coordinate-specific validation after updating the test/metadata, or close the request if no meaningful reachability metadata/test can be justified."}}
